Aminabad Agriculture Complex (, also Romanized as Mojtame` Keshāvarzī Āmīnābād) is a village and agriculture complex in Momenabad Rural District, in the Central District of Sarbisheh County, South Khorasan Province, Iran. According to the 2006 census, it had a population was 94, residing in 32 families.
